LimitedTimeEvalFunction - Class in popt4jlib
The class is a wrapper class for FunctionIntf objects, that forces the function to execute in a different thread than the calling thread, allowing only up to a certain amount of time for execution.
LimitedTimeEvalFunction(FunctionIntf, long) - Constructor for class popt4jlib.LimitedTimeEvalFunction
public constructor, setting up a LimitedTimeTaskExecutor object that allows running tasks for up to millis2wait milliseconds in different threads in the executor's thread-pool.
LimitedTimeTaskExecutor - Class in parallel
A class that allows its users to execute tasks (object that describe some computation that must implement the TaskObject interface) for a limited time, starting them in different threads than the thread that called the execute(task) method.
